org.hackystat.sensor.eclipse
Class EclipseSensor

java.lang.Object
  org.hackystat.sensor.eclipse.EclipseSensor

public class EclipseSensor
extends java.lang.Object

Provides all the necessary sensor initialization and collects data in this singleton class. A client can use one static method to get this instance:

A client can set Eclipse sensor by calling getInstance(), ant can use the following process methods: Because of lazy instantiation, any activity was not set until the initial call for getInstance().

Author:
Hongbing Kou, Takuya Yamashita

addDevEvent

public void addDevEvent(java.lang.String type,
                        java.net.URI fileResource,
                        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> moreKeyValueMap,
                        java.lang.String message)
Processes development events that occur within the Eclipse browser. The Browser event classes will invoke this method to process the development event and send the data to Hackystat.

Parameters:
type - The type of development event, eg "ProgramUnit:New".
fileResource - The associated path with the event, may be file or directory.
moreKeyValueMap - Additional development event data, eg "unit-name=EclipseSensor".
message - DevEvent message to be used for logging and display.

processBuffTrans

public void processBuffTrans()
Process the buffer transition to check if the current buffer is visiting a file and if that file is different from the file visited by the buffer during the last wakeup. Its element consists of the the (absolute) file name (or last-time-visited file name) from which an user is visiting, the (absolute) file name (or current-visiting file name) to which the user is visiting, and the modification status of the last-time-visited file.
